---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="CapitalBench Privacy"
  description="CapitalBench privacy note for website analytics, contribution links, and public benchmark data."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Privacy"
    title="Analytics And Data Use"
    summary="CapitalBench uses analytics to understand aggregate site usage and improve the public benchmark website."
  />

  <section class="section doc-layout">
    <article class="doc-main">
      <h2>Website Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        CapitalBench uses Google Analytics to measure aggregate traffic, page views, referral sources, and selected
        product interactions such as repository clicks, round-detail views, methodology clicks, and Stripe contribution
        link clicks.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Do Not Send</h2>
      <p>
        CapitalBench does not intentionally send provider API keys, raw provider responses, raw model prompts, full
        model outputs, payment details, email addresses, or private operational secrets to Google Analytics.
      </p>

      <h2>Contribution Payments</h2>
      <p>
        Contribution checkout is handled by Stripe. CapitalBench tracks outbound contribution link clicks for aggregate
        funnel measurement, but Stripe handles card details, receipts, billing records, and payment processing.
      </p>

      <h2>Email Updates</h2>
      <p>
        If you subscribe through the website, CapitalBench stores your email address in the Website Collection audience
        so we can send occasional benchmark updates and future product announcements. You can unsubscribe from these
        emails at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>Public Benchmark Data</h2>
      <p>
        Round inputs, official model decisions, audit hashes, score status, and public benchmark reports are published
        as part of the benchmark's audit surface. The privacy boundary here concerns website analytics and payment
        handling, not public benchmark artifacts.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="methodology-aside" aria-label="Privacy summary">
      <div class="rail-panel">
        <span class="metric-label">Analytics</span>
        <h3>Always On</h3>
        <p>Google Analytics loads when the production measurement ID is configured.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rail-panel">
        <span class="metric-label">Payments</span>
        <h3>Stripe Hosted</h3>
        <p>Payment details are handled by Stripe-hosted checkout, not by this website.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rail-panel">
        <span class="metric-label">Email</span>
        <h3>Email Only</h3>
        <p>Website subscriptions collect an email address for occasional CapitalBench updates.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rail-panel">
        <span class="metric-label">Event Scope</span>
        <h3>Safe Parameters</h3>
        <p>Events use limited fields such as page path, round ID, contribution tier, cadence, and link domain.</p>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
